data.enText: happening at the end of a long process

data.chText: 我们最终的目的 / 目标
无论出什么事情，我们愿承担全部责任。
data.enText: We will accept ultimate responsibility for whatever happens.

data.chText: 最后的决定权握在父母手中。
data.enText: The ultimate decision lies with the parents.

data.chText: 极端的；最好（或坏、伟大、重要等）的
data.enText: most extreme; best, worst, greatest, most important, etc.

data.chText: 这次竞赛将是对你的技能的最大考验。
data.enText: This race will be the ultimate test of your skill.

data.chText: 丝绸床单乃是极度的奢侈品。
data.enText: Silk sheets are the ultimate luxury.

data.chText: 根本的；基本的；基础性的
哲学与科学的终极原理
data.enText: the ultimate truths of philosophy and science

data.chText: 最好（或先进、伟大等）的事物；极品；精华
data.enText: the best, most advanced, greatest, etc. of its kind

means: 最好(或坏、伟大、重要等)的
最好(或先进、伟大等)的事物

tr: the finest or most superior quality of its kind
being the last or concluding element of a series
example: the ultimate sonata of that opus
a distinction between the verb and noun senses of `conflict' is that in the verb the stress is on the ultimate (or last) syllable

tr: furthest or highest in degree or order

value.def: You use ultimate to describe the final result or aim of a long series of events.

example.ex: He said it is still not possible to predict the ultimate outcome...
example.tran: 他说现在还无法预料最终的结局。

example.ex: The ultimate aim is to expand the network further.
example.tran: 最终目的是为了进一步拓展该网络。

value.def: You use ultimate to describe the original source or cause of something.

example.ex: Plants are the ultimate source of all foodstuffs...
example.tran: 植物是所有食物的最根本来源。

example.ex: The ultimate cause of what's happened seems to have been the advertising campaign.
example.tran: 出事的最根本原因似乎在于那场广告宣传活动。

value.tran: 最根本的；最基础的；最原始的

value.def: You use ultimate to describe the most important or powerful thing of a particular kind.

example.ex: ...the ultimate power of the central government...
Of course, the ultimate authority remained the presidency...
example.tran: 当然，拥有最高权力者依然是总统。

example.ex: My experience as player, coach and manager has prepared me for this ultimate challenge.
example.tran: 当球员、教练和主教练的经历锻炼了我，使我能够应对这一终极挑战。

value.tran: 最重要的；最强大的；至高的

value.def: You use ultimate to describe the most extreme and unpleasant example of a particular thing.

example.ex: Being removed from his post during operations is the ultimate humiliation for a ship's captain.
example.tran: 在执行任务的过程中被免职，这对一位船长来说是莫大的耻辱。
背叛是最不可饶恕的罪孽。

example.ex: Coleman lives in fear of the ultimate disgrace.
example.tran: 科尔曼整天担心会颜面尽失。

value.tran: 极端的；极度的；令人极其不快的

value.def: You use ultimate to describe the best possible example of a particular thing.

example.ex: He is the ultimate English gentleman...
example.tran: 他是最最典型的英国绅士。

example.ex: Caviar and oysters on ice are generally considered the ultimate luxury foods.
example.tran: 一般认为，鱼子酱和冰镇牡蛎是顶级美味。

value.def: The ultimate in something is the best or most advanced example of it.

example.ex: Ballet is the ultimate in human movement...
example.tran: 芭蕾舞在人类的动作中可谓优雅至极。

example.ex: This hotel is the ultimate in luxury...
Working from home offers the ultimate in flexible life styles.
example.tran: 在家办公为人们提供了极其灵活的生活方式。
